INVESTIGATING officers from the Family Violence Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit in Uitenhage would like to make an urgent appeal to members of the community to assist them in locating a missing 13-year-old girl. Police spokesperson Captain Gerda Swart said Tholithuba-Elihle Magasana was officially reported missing by her caretaker on Saturday, June 29 after she did not return to the Youth Centre. “She was last seen at 18:00 on the day she went missing and she was wearing a white shirt with blue jeans. Magasana is about 1,55m tall and weighs 80kg,” she said. Anyone with information about her whereabouts is urged to contact the investigating officer, Detective Sergeant Mbulelo Lamani on 071 352 4798 or SAPS Crime Stop 08600 10111.